WHOLE TIME, I’ve always been THEE one🥰 I know and accept that now. I most definitely deserve the life I expect. All aspects and every micro detail of it♥️I love me for knowing and learning it starts with me❣️

For years, I hid my true self inside of relationships (platonic or romantic). I’m so comfortable and happy with myself and truly accept all parts of me (actively getting better at this). I personally feel like I would overdo it/oversell myself to seem “worthy” to them.
So now, in this stage/level of dating myself, I am going to process and see which ways I truly like to receive intimacy. And then give it to myself with a smile and happy heart♥️♥️

You ever just want to pick up the phone and talk about your day with your partner? Or go home and cuddle on the couch, listen and respond to each other? Like that’s the type of intimacy and affection I miss.

I love being in a romantic relationship and sharing my happiness with somebody.. so when I’m in the “hangman” stage of dating, it lowkey saddens me🥺 but 5 months strong of dating and TRULY giving myself the things I desire in a romantic relationship has also been so refreshing.
